Abstract = {{Pathogens have been implicated as potential factors in the recent
   decline of some North American bumble bee (Bombus) species, but little
   information has been reported about the natural enemy complex of bumble
   bees in the United States. We targeted bumble bee populations in a
   state-wide survey in Illinois and several sites in California and Oregon
   where declines have been reported to determine presence and prevalence
