   poricidal anthers and are pollinated by bees. The study sought to
   analyse potential pollinators of both plants during visits to their
   flowers in a restinga area in Bahia. The flowering displayed by both
   species was considered continuous and long duration, constantly
   providing pollen to floral visitors. C. ovalifolia was visited by 17
   species of bees and C. ramosa by 16 species, predominantly from the
