   varied between 0.08 to 0.62 (average 0.34) and the discriminating power
   (D) ranged from 0.61 to 0.99 (average 0.85). The observed heterozygosity
   (HO) and the expected heterozygosity (HE) ranged from 0.04 to 1.00 and
