Month = {{JUL-AUG}},
Abstract = {{We conducted a comparative analysis of bee-plant and wasp-plant
   interaction networks, aiming at the identification of similarities and
   differences between networks of flower-visiting groups with direct or
   indirect mutualism with plants. We measured for each network: number of
   social bees and social wasps, number of plants visited (P), degree of
   nestedness, number of observed (I) and possible interactions,
   connectance (C), and interaction density (D). The network formed by
